FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FMr Martin said Mr Carney's
OL,7,Fgrandparents, who were born in
OL,8,FAughagower, would be "enormously
OL,9,Fproud" that their "sacrifices and
OL,10,Fhardships paved the way for his
OL,11,Fremarkable accomplishments and
OL,12,Fachievements".
OL,14,FAt an event at Dublin Castle on
OL,15,FSaturday, the Taoiseach suggested that
OL,16,Fthe prime minister's historical ties
OL,17,Fto Ireland stretch back even further.
OL,26,@pD@VOUqD@FO]qD@SOUtD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FHe said that after visiting the Book
OL,7,Fof Kells in Trinity College, the two
OL,8,Fmen saw a page in the Book of Armagh
OL,9,Fthat linked Aughagower to the
OL,10,Fcountry's patron saint.
OL,12,FMr Martin said: "The page opened for
OL,13,FTirechan's account of St Patrick's
OL,14,Fjourney through Mayo and he visits `
OL,15,Fyou won't believe it ` Aughagower
OL,16,Fbefore going to Croagh Patrick."
OL,26,@tD@QOUuD@BrtuD@GrpxD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FHe added: "In that paragraph, Patrick
OL,7,Fconsecrates a church in that place,
OL,8,FAughagower, with the maiden Mathona,
OL,9,Fwho's clearly setting up, we think, a
OL,10,Fnunnery there.
OL,12,F"And Patrick said to the people
OL,13,Fgathered 'there will be good bishops
OL,14,Fhere, and from their seed, blessed
OL,15,Fpeople will come forth forever in this
OL,16,Fsea'."
OL,26,@nD@KOUtD@AOUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FMr Martin went on to joke: "I knew he
OL,7,Fwas a visionary, but I never quite
OL,8,Fknew that St Patrick was that
OL,9,Fvisionary ` and he clearly had Mark
OL,10,FCarney in mind."
OL,12,FThe Taoiseach also referenced the
OL,13,F"extraordinary journey" of Mr Carney's
OL,14,Fgrandparents in search of a better
OL,15,Flife across the Atlantic.
OL,17,F"They could scarcely have imagined
OL,18,Fthat one day their grandson would
OL,19,Freturn to Ireland as Prime Minister of
OL,20,FCanada, welcomed by the people of the
OL,21,Fcountry they left behind."
OL,26,@nD@\OUrD@PO]uD@AOUuD@WO]yD@AOU}D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FHe told Mr Carney that when he walks
OL,7,Fthe roads his grandparents walked in
OL,8,FMayo, he would discover that "Ireland
OL,9,Fnever forgets her own".
OL,11,FReferencing the poem Thresholds by
OL,12,FIrish poet John O'Donohue, Mr Carney
OL,13,Ftold the same event: "My grandparents
OL,14,Fcrossed their threshold in Mayo a
OL,15,Fcentury ago ` into a life of a country
OL,16,Fthat was still building itself, as
OL,17,FCanada always has.
OL,19,F"And they were part of four and a half
OL,20,Fmillion Canadians who are the product
OL,21,Fof similar decisions."
OL,26,@pD@^OUqD@VO]uD@VOU{D@AOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,FHe added: "Today, half a million
OL,7,Fpeople who travel between our
OL,8,Fcountries every year cross thresholds.
OL,10,F"Now, there's one other threshold that
OL,11,FI'll mention at which Canada, Ireland,
OL,12,FEurope now stand ` and that's the
OL,13,Frupture in the global system.
OL,15,F"From rules-based to arms-based, from
OL,16,Fright to might, from values to
OL,17,Fvanquished.
OL,26,@nD@KOUrD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1781408877
OL,3,CMark Carney to return 'home' in Mayo
OL,4,Cvisit
OL,6,F"Where will we go, and to what
OL,7,Fpurpose? And I'd suggest that the
OL,8,Fthresholds that we have crossed and
OL,9,Fthose before us have crossed, the
OL,10,Fshared values that have been forged in
OL,11,Fdoing so, will bring us forward."
OL,13,FOn Saturday, the two leaders announced
OL,14,Fa new "bilateral co-operation
OL,15,Fframework" on trade and investment,
OL,16,Flife sciences, research and
OL,17,Finnovation, and security and defence.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@aO]vD@GOUwD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/9
